The latest stable MSTest is **4.2.3**. Here are the breaking changes relevant to your code:

## Key Breaking Change: `[ExpectedException]` is removed

Your two test methods use `[ExpectedException(...)]`, which no longer exists in v4. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

## Other notable v4 breaking changes (not affecting your current code, but worth knowing):

| Change | Impact |
|--------|--------|
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Remove `ClassCleanupBehavior.EndOfClass` parameter from `[ClassCleanup]` |
| `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` → `ExecuteAsync` | Only if you have custom `TestMethodAttribute` subclasses |
| `Assert` message+params APIs simplified | Use string interpolation instead of `message, params object[]` |
| `TestContext.Properties` is now `IDictionary<string, object>` | Use `.ContainsKey()` instead of `.Contains()` |
| `TestTimeout` enum removed | Use `[Timeout(int.MaxValue)]` instead of `[Timeout(TestTimeout.Infinite)]` |
| Minimum .NET target is net8.0 | Your project already targets net8.0 ✓ |

## To upgrade

Update your `.csproj`:
```xml
<PackageReference Include="MSTest" Version="4.2.3" />
```

Would you like me to apply these changes to your project?
